  title `Collector may entrust any part of his duties to his Deputy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00076_1856-18_1659084451530&sectionId=67576&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00076_1856-18_1659084451530
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the Collector`
  line `of Calcutta to employ any Deputy Collector subordinate to him, in the performance of any part of the duties`
  line `of his office under the said Regulation, or under Act XI of 1849, or Act XXIII of 1850; and all Rules,`
  line `Regulations, and Acts relating to the office of Deputy Collector, shall be of the same force within the Town`
  line `of Calcutta as in other parts of the territories subject to the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
